.TH "crc8" 9 "crc8" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
crc8 \- calculate a crc8 over the given input data.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "u8" crc8
.BI "(const u8 table[CRC8_TABLE_SIZE] "  ","
.BI "u8 *pdata "  ","
.BI "size_t nbytes "  ","
.BI "u8 crc "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "table" 12
crc table used for calculation.
.IP "pdata" 12
pointer to data buffer.
.IP "nbytes" 12
number of bytes in data buffer.
.IP "crc" 12
previous returned crc8 value.
